<topic id='business_definition_nhs_allied_health_professional_service__referral_to_treatment_measurement_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: NHS Allied Health Professional Service (Referral To Treatment Measurement) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_allied_health_professional_service__referral_to_treatment_measurement_">NHS Allied Health Professional Service (Referral To Treatment Measurement)</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
An 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_allied_health_professional_service__referral_to_treatment_measurement_">NHS Allied Health Professional Service (Referral To Treatment Measurement)</xref>
 is a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_service">SERVICE</xref>
 involving the treatment of a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 by one of the following types of Allied Health Professional:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
Art Therapists, Music Therapists and Dramatherapists (
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_arts_therapist">Arts Therapists</xref>
)        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_chiropodist">Chiropodists</xref>
            <p>
/
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_chiropodist">Podiatrist</xref>
s        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_dietitian">Dietitians</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_occupational_therapist">Occupational Therapists</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_orthoptist">Orthoptists</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_physiotherapist">Physiotherapists</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_prosthetist">Prosthetists</xref>
         <p>
 and 
            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_orthotist">Orthotists</xref>
         </p>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_radiographer">Radiographers</xref>
         <p> (Diagnostic and Therapeutic)</p>
      </li>
      <li>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_speech_and_language_therapist">Speech and Language Therapists</xref>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>
Where the Allied Health Professional works in a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_community_health_service">Community Health Service</xref>
, the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 requires their 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_allied_health_professional_referral_to_treatment_measurement">Allied Health Professional Referral To Treatment Measurement</xref>
 activity to be reported in the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet" keyref="dataset_community_services_data_set">Community Services Data Set</xref>
.   </p>
  <p>
Where the Allied Health Professional activity took place at an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_out-patient_clinic">Out-Patient Clinic</xref>
, the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_allied_health_professional_referral_to_treatment_measurement">Allied Health Professional Referral To Treatment Measurement</xref>
 activity must be reported in the 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_cds_v6-2_type_020_-_outpatient_cds">CDS V6-2 Type 020 - Outpatient Commissioning Data Set</xref>
.  In addition to this, where an Allied Health Professional sees a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 on a 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
 but the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITY</xref>
 is not related to the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_hospital_provider_spell">Hospital Provider Spell</xref>
 the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 is being treated under, this should be regarded as replacing an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment_non-consultant">Out-Patient Appointment Non-Consultant</xref>
, and a 
    <xref outputclass="dataSet"
            keyref="dataset_cds_v6-2_type_020_-_outpatient_cds">CDS V6-2 Type 020 - Outpatient Commissioning Data Set</xref>
 record should flow.  
    <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_activity_location_type_code">ACTIVITY LOCATION TYPE CODE</xref>
 may be submitted to allow identification of this Allied Health Professional 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_activity">ACTIVITY</xref>
.  For example, if a 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_chiropodist">Podiatrist</xref>
 were asked to see a patient who was currently admitted for a condition where the agreed care pathway did not include Podiatry services, then an 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_out-patient_appointment_non-consultant">Out-Patient Appointment Non-Consultant</xref>
 should be recorded, with the 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_activity_location_type_code">ACTIVITY LOCATION TYPE CODE</xref>
 of E02 
    <i>'</i>
      <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_ward">WARD</xref>
      <i>'</i>
, and the relevant Referral To Treatment data items also completed.  </p>
  <p>
Further guidance relating to Allied Health Professional Referral To Treatment initiative can be found on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_department_of_health_and_social_care">Department of Health and Social Care</xref>
 part of the gov.uk website at: the 
    <xref href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/revised-guide-for-referral-to-treatment-for-allied-health-professionals"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Revised guide for referral to treatment for allied health professionals</xref>
.  </p>

